INSTALL:

1. Install boost library first.
   a. cd to boost_1_55_0 directory.
   b. chmod +x bootstrap.sh
   c. chmod +x tools/build/v2/engine/build.sh
   d. ./bootstrap.sh --with-libraries=filesystem,regex,thread --prefix=/usr/local
   e. chmod +x ./b2
   f. ./b2 install
   g. ldconfig


FAQ:
Q: failed to compile lua
A: If you're running Linux and get compilation errors, make sure you have installed the readline development package. If you get link errors after that, then try "make linux MYLIBS=-ltermcap".
